          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2017-11-28 09:45:26" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>= action by which humans or deities provide assistance or support to (other) humans ► in order to make their life, work, task  or situation easier</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to help</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to assist</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to support</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>(1) When verb has a human subject, it is often used in a military or political-national context, which connects with the substantive uses of the verb to refer to allies: 'helper'/'ally'. (2) Is also used in a socio-legal context, with both human and divine subjects, to refer to the activity of protecting or defending someone as 'defender'.</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
